## What CTI Is Not

CTI is **not** a foundation model, an agent, a prompt wrapper, a dashboard, or a traditional benchmark.

## What CTI Aims to Be

- A **cognitive observability infrastructure**
- An **operational theory** of cognitive throughput
- An **open standard** for measuring intelligent systems
- A **universal layer** of cognitive optimization

---

## Open System Philosophy

CTI is proposed as an open framework, an open research system, and a collaborative ecosystem based on RFCs.

The goal is not proprietary control. The goal is to allow **anyone to contribute to building an operational science of measurable cognition**.

---

## Why This Matters

The next generation of intelligent systems will not be defined solely by larger models, more memory, or more computational power.

It will be defined by systems capable of:

- Optimizing decisions
- Reducing cognitive friction
- Increasing operational throughput under real constraints

